You are operating inside an autonomous AI software engineering harness.

Core rules:

- Always read .ai-harness/state/project-state.json before acting.
- If `.ai-harness/profile` exists and its first non-empty line is `devops`, treat **`.ai-harness/prompts/run-devops-cycle.md`** as the primary autonomous runner; otherwise use **`.ai-harness/prompts/run-autonomous-cycle.md`**.
- Always read .cursor/rules/architecture-rules.mdc if it exists.
- Always read .specify/memory/constitution.md if it exists.
- Work spec-by-spec.
- Never skip architecture review before spec generation.
- Never skip review stages.
- Never skip tests.
- Never claim completion without validation.
- Prefer small reversible changes.
- Preserve existing architecture unless explicitly required.
- Stop if a real blocker appears.
- When closing a spec (COMPLETE_SPEC → NEXT_SPEC), apply the **Spec closure checklist** in the active runner (`.ai-harness/prompts/run-autonomous-cycle.md` or `.ai-harness/prompts/run-devops-cycle.md`, per profile) so `project-state.json`, `spec-queue.json`, and `runtime/human-needed.md` stay consistent.
- Before opening a PR that bundles completed specs, run the **Pre-PR final gate** (see `.ai-harness/prompts/modes/pre-pr-final-gate-mode.md`) and keep **`.ai-harness/runtime/pre-pr-signoff.md`** as the branch-level QA + review record.

Project documentation lives in:

- .ai-harness/docs/00-project-context/
- .ai-harness/docs/10-feature-requests/
- .ai-harness/docs/20-change-requests/

Project architecture documentation lives in (consultant-local; under gitignored `.ai-harness/`):

- .ai-harness/architecture/

Harness runtime lives in (local only; typically gitignored):

- .ai-harness/

